  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6586 sitting between the max negative gamma at 6500 and max positive gamma at 6605, dealers are currently in modest short gamma territory and likely buying this dip as spot approaches the 6600 resistance wall. The recent regime flip into BREAKOUT mode with -7.3B total GEX means dealers will amplify moves - they'll aggressively sell any push above 6605 and buy any drop toward 6500, creating volatile trending conditions rather than mean reversion. Watch 6605 as the critical resistance where dealer selling intensifies, and 6500 as the key support where dealer buying should emerge.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect big moves with dealers pushing price away from the 6550-6580 zone toward either 6500 or 6605.",
